<IN>
ALUMINUM (ALU)
</IN>
<LP>
   PITTSBURGH -- Aluminum Co. of America said it closed its
last bauxite mines in the U.S., resulting in the layoffs or
retirements of 200 employees. The mines, in Saline County,
Ark., are adjacent to Alcoa's bauxite refinery and alumina
chemical facilities.
   The company said the mining and refining operations were
shut down because of insufficient reserves of bauxite.
</LP>
