<HL>
   New Car Sales in Britain in May
</HL>
<DATE>
06/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   F GM EUROP
</CO>
<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
AUTOMOBILES (AUT)
</IN>
<LP>
   LONDON -- May new-car sales in Britain, measured by
registrations, totaled 173,896, a 13% decline from a year
earlier but a 4.2% rise from April, the Society of Motor
Manufacturers and Traders Ltd. said.
   Imports took a 55% share of the market in May, down from
58% in April and 56% a year earlier. Total imports, including
cars produced overseas by British manufacturers, fell 1% to
95,207 in May, compared with the previous month, and were off
14% from a year earlier.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co., Dearborn, Mich., sold 47,996 cars in May,
up 11% from April but down 12% from a year earlier. Ford's
market share was 28%, up from 26% in April and unchanged from
a year earlier. Detroit-based General Motors Corp.'s May
sales advanced 9.7% to 27,685, compared with April, and
slipped 8.9% from a year earlier. GM's market share edged up
to 16% from 15% both in April and a year earlier.
</TEXT>
