   USAir's Traffic Fell in May
</HL>
<DATE>
06/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C12
</SO>
<CO>
   U
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   ARLINGTON, Va. -- USAir, a unit of USAir Group Inc., said
its May traffic declined less than 1% to 2.97 billion revenue
passenger miles from 2.98 billion a year earlier. A revenue
passenger mile is one paying passenger flown one mile.
   The carrier's May load factor, or the percentage of
available seats occupied, fell to 58.9% from 62.8%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   For the first five months of this year, USAir's traffic
rose 5.8% to 14.23 billion revenue passenger miles from 13.45
billion a year earlier. The load factor fell to 58.7% from
59.1%.
