<HL>
   Japan's Imported Vehicle Sales
</HL>
<DATE>
06/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   JAPAN
</CO>
<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<LP>
   TOKYO -- Sales of imported cars, trucks and buses in Japan
increased 21.4% in May from a year earlier to 16,325 units, a
record for the month, the Japan Automobile Importers'
Association said.
   May marked the 77th consecutive month of year-to-year
sales growth. The latest rise was led by sales of midsized
cars from West Germany and the U.S. Sales of imported
passenger cars totaled 16,152 units in May, up 21.3% from a
year earlier, and accounting for 99% of overall import sales.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In the first five months of this year, sales of imported
vehicles grew 43.9% to 91,369 units from a year earlier.
Sales of passenger cars totaled 90,485 units, also up 43.9%.
</TEXT>
