<LP>
   Reed International PLC, a British publishing company, said
pretax profit for the year ended March 31 rose 11% to #302
million ($509.3 million) from #271 million a year earlier, at
the top of market expectations and boosted by strong results
in the enlarged U.S. business publishing unit.
   Sales edged up 1.5% to #1.58 billion from #1.55 billion.
</LP>
