   Increases of 11% also were posted in profit after taxes
and minority interests to #211.3 million from #189.7 million,
and earnings per share to 38.2 pence from 34.5 pence. Net
profit attributable to shareholders fell 55% to #211 million
from #498 million; the year-earlier figure was boosted by an
extraordinary gain of #308.4 million largely from the sale of
a business.
   In the U.S., where, among other acquisitions last year,
Reed in November paid $303.7 million to buy the legal
publisher Martindale-Hubbell Inc., operating profit on
business publishing soared 76% to #80.2 million, and sales
increased 45% to #464 million.
