<LP>
   TOKYO -- Motorola Inc. said the Japanese government had,
as expected, officially chosen its digital voice technology
for part of Japan's emerging digital mobile-phone standard.
   As reported, Motorola's coding technology last month
performed best in tests conducted by a division of the
Ministry of Post and Telecommunications. Seven other
companies, including Nippon Telegraph &amp; Telephone Co.,
participated in the contest.
